  "prompt": "How many keywords are there in the COBOL programming language in the latest version?",
  "response": "As of the latest standards for COBOL in 2014 (COBOL 2014), there are 60 reserved keywords in the programming language. These keywords are part of the reserved word list and are predefined by the language syntax. \n\nHowever, the COBOL language specification and standards may have updates or revisions beyond this point, and the number of keywords could change with new versions. Therefore, for the most definitive and current count, checking the latest COBOL standards documentation from an authoritative source such as ISO or the community managing COBOL standards is recommended.",
